==Events== * [[43 BC]] &ndash; [[Battle of Forum Gallorum]]: [[Mark Antony]], besieging [[Julius Caesar|Caesar]]'s assassin [[Decimus Junius Brutus Albinus|Decimus Brutus]] in [[Mutina]], defeats the forces of the consul [[Gaius Vibius Pansa Caetronianus|Pansa]], but is then immediately defeated by the army of the other consul, [[Aulus Hirtius]]. * [[AD 69]] &ndash; [[Vitellius]], commander of the [[Rhine]] armies, defeats [[Roman emperor|Emperor]] [[Otho]] in the [[Battle of Bedriacum]] and seizes the throne. * [[AD 70]] &ndash; [[Siege of Jerusalem (AD 70)|Siege of Jerusalem]]: [[Titus]], son of emperor [[Vespasian]], surrounds the Jewish capital with four [[Roman legion]]s. * [[193]] &ndash; [[Septimius Severus]] is proclaimed [[Roman emperor]] by the army in [[Illyricum (Roman province)|Illyricum]] (in the [[Balkans]]). * [[966]] &ndash; After his marriage to the Christian [[Doubravka of Bohemia]], the [[paganism|pagan]] ruler of the [[Polans (western)|Polans]], [[Mieszko I of Poland|Mieszko&nbsp;I]], [[Baptism of Poland|converts to Christianity]], an event considered to be the [[History of Poland during the Piast dynasty|founding of the Polish state]]. * [[972]] &ndash; Co-Emperor [[Otto II, Holy Roman Emperor|Otto II]], a son of [[Otto I, Holy Roman Emperor|Otto I]] (the Great), marries the Byzantine princess [[Theophanu]]. She is crowned empress by Pope [[Pope John XIII|John XIII]] at [[Rome]]. *[[1028]] &ndash; [[Henry III, Holy Roman Emperor|Henry III]], son of [[Conrad II, Holy Roman Emperor|Conrad]], is elected [[King of Germany]]. *[[1205]] &ndash; [[Battle of Adrianople (1205)|Battle of Adrianople]] between [[Bulgarians]] and [[Crusaders]]. *[[1294]] &ndash; [[Temür Khan|Temür]], grandson of [[Kublai]], is elected [[Khagan]] of the [[Mongols]] and Emperor of the [[Yuan dynasty]] with the reigning titles Oljeitu and Chengzong. *[[1341]] &ndash; Sack of [[Saluzzo]] (Italy) by Italian-Angevine troops under [[Manfred V, Marquess of Saluzzo]]. *[[1434]] &ndash; The foundation stone of [[Nantes Cathedral]], France is laid. *[[1471]] &ndash; In England, the [[Yorkists]] under [[Edward IV of England|Edward IV]] defeat the [[House of Lancaster|Lancastrians]] under the [[Richard Neville, 16th Earl of Warwick|Earl of Warwick]] at the [[Battle of Barnet]]; the Earl is killed and [[Edward IV]] resumes the throne. *[[1561]] &ndash; A [[1561 celestial phenomenon over Nuremberg|celestial phenomenon]] is reported over Nuremberg, described as an aerial battle. *[[1639]] &ndash; Imperial forces are defeated by the Swedes at the [[Battle of Chemnitz]]. The Swedish victory prolongs the [[Thirty Years' War]] and allows them to advance into [[Bohemia]]. *[[1699]] &ndash; [[Khalsa]]: The [[Sikh]] religion was formalised as the [[Khalsa]] - the brotherhood of Warrior-Saints - by [[Guru Gobind Singh]] in northern India, in accordance with the [[Nanakshahi calendar]]. *[[1775]] &ndash; The first [[Abolitionism in the United States|abolition]] society in North America is established. The [[Pennsylvania Abolition Society|Society for the Relief of Free Negroes Unlawfully Held in Bondage]] is organized in [[Philadelphia]] by [[Benjamin Franklin]] and [[Benjamin Rush]]. *[[1793]] &ndash; The French troops led by [[Léger-Félicité Sonthonax]] defeat the slaves settlers in the [[Siege of Port-au-Prince (1793)|Siege of Port-au-Prince]]. *[[1816]] &ndash; [[Bussa]], a slave in British-ruled [[Barbados]], leads a slave rebellion and is killed. For this, he is remembered as the first national hero of [[Barbados]]. *[[1828]] &ndash; [[Noah Webster]] copyrights the first edition of [[Webster's Dictionary|his dictionary]]. *[[1849]] &ndash; Hungary [[Hungarian Declaration of Independence|declares itself independent]] of [[Austrian Empire|Austria]] with [[Lajos Kossuth]] as its leader. *[[1865]] &ndash; U.S. President [[Abraham Lincoln]] is [[Assassination of Abraham Lincoln|shot]] in [[Ford's Theatre]] by [[John Wilkes Booth]]; Lincoln died the next day. * 1865 &ndash; [[United States Secretary of State|U.S. Secretary of State]] [[William H. Seward]] and his family are attacked at home by [[Lewis Powell (conspirator)|Lewis Powell]]. *[[1881]] &ndash; The [[Four Dead in Five Seconds Gunfight]] is fought in [[El Paso, Texas]]. *[[1890]] &ndash; The [[Pan-American Union]] is founded by the First [[International Conference of American States]] in Washington, D.C. *[[1894]] &ndash; The first ever commercial [[film|motion picture]] house opened in New York City using ten [[Kinetoscope]]s, a device for peep-show viewing of films. *[[1900]] &ndash; The [[Exposition Universelle (1900)|Exposition Universelle]] begins. *[[1902]] &ndash; [[James Cash Penney]] opens his [[J. C. Penney|first store]] in [[Kemmerer, Wyoming]].<ref>{{Cite web |url=https://shsmo.org/historicmissourians/name/p/penney/ |title=J. C. Penney |website=Historic Missourians |publisher=State Historical Society of Missouri |access-date=2018-04-11}}</ref> *[[1906]] &ndash; The [[Azusa Street Revival]] opens and will launch [[Pentecostalism]] as a worldwide movement. *[[1908]] &ndash; [[Hauser Dam]], a [[steel dam]] on the [[Missouri River]] in [[Montana]], U.S., fails, sending a surge of water {{convert|25|to|30|ft}} high downstream. *[[1909]] &ndash; [[Adana massacre|A massacre]] is organized by the [[Ottoman Empire]] against the Armenian population of [[Cilicia]]. *[[1912]] &ndash; The British passenger liner {{RMS|Titanic}} hits an iceberg in the North Atlantic at 23:40 (sinks morning of April 15th). *[[1927]] &ndash; The first [[Volvo]] car premieres in [[Gothenburg]], Sweden. *[[1928]] &ndash; The [[Bremen (aircraft)|Bremen]], a German [[Junkers W 33]] type aircraft, reaches [[Greenly Island, Canada]] - the first successful transatlantic aeroplane flight from east to west. *[[1931]] &ndash; The [[Cortes Generales|Spanish Cortes]] deposes King [[Alfonso XIII of Spain|Alfonso XIII]] and proclaims the [[Second Spanish Republic]]. *[[1935]] &ndash; The [[Black Sunday (storm)|Black Sunday dust storm]], considered one of the worst storms of the [[Dust Bowl]], swept across the Oklahoma and Texas panhandles and neighboring areas. *[[1939]] &ndash; ''[[The Grapes of Wrath]]'', by American author [[John Steinbeck]] is first published by the [[Viking Press]]. *[[1940]] &ndash; [[World War II]]: [[Royal Marines]] land in [[Namsos]], Norway in preparation for a larger force to arrive two days later. *[[1941]] &ndash; World War II: German general [[Erwin Rommel]] attacks [[Siege of Tobruk|Tobruk]]. *[[1942]] &ndash; [[Malta]] receives the [[George Cross]] for its gallantry. The [[George Cross]] was given by King [[George VI]] himself and is now an emblem on the [[Flag of Malta|Maltese national flag]]. *[[1944]] &ndash; [[1944 Bombay explosion|Bombay explosion]]: A massive explosion in [[Bombay]] harbor kills 300 and causes economic damage valued then at 20 million pounds. *[[1945]] &ndash; [[Razing of Friesoythe]]: The [[4th Canadian (Armoured) Division]] [[Razing of Friesoythe|deliberately destroyed]] the German town of [[Friesoythe]] on the orders of [[Major general|Major General]] [[Christopher Vokes]]. *[[1958]] &ndash; The [[Soviet Union|Soviet]] satellite [[Sputnik 2]] falls from orbit after a mission duration of 162 days. This was the first spacecraft to carry a living animal, a [[Soviet space dogs|female dog]] named [[Laika]], who likely lived only a few hours. *[[1967]] &ndash; [[Gnassingbé Eyadéma]] overthrows [[President of Togo]] [[Nicolas Grunitzky]] and installs himself as the new president, a title he would hold for the next 38 years. *[[1978]] &ndash; [[1978 Tbilisi Demonstrations|Tbilisi Demonstrations]]: Thousands of [[Georgia (country)|Georgians]] demonstrate against Soviet attempts to change the constitutional status of the [[Georgian language]]. *[[1981]] &ndash; [[STS-1]]: The first operational [[Space Shuttle]], ''[[Space Shuttle Columbia|Columbia]]'' completes its first test flight. *[[1986]] &ndash; The heaviest [[hailstone]]s ever recorded ({{convert|1|kg|lb}}) fall on the [[Gopalganj District, Bangladesh|Gopalganj district of Bangladesh]], killing 92. *[[1988]] &ndash; The {{USS|Samuel B. Roberts|FFG-58|6}} strikes a [[naval mine|mine]] in the [[Persian Gulf]] during [[Operation Earnest Will]]. * 1988 &ndash; In a [[United Nations]] ceremony in [[Geneva]], [[Switzerland]], the [[Soviet Union]] signs an agreement pledging to withdraw its troops from [[Afghanistan]]. *[[1991]] &ndash; The [[Georgia (country)|Republic of Georgia]] introduces the post of [[President of Georgia|President]] after its declaration of independence from the Soviet Union. *[[1994]] &ndash; In a U.S. [[friendly fire]] incident during [[Operation Provide Comfort]] in northern [[Iraq]], two [[United States Air Force]] aircraft mistakenly [[1994 Black Hawk shootdown incident|shoot-down]] two United States Army helicopters, killing 26 people. *[[1999]] &ndash; [[NATO]] mistakenly bombs a convoy of ethnic [[Albania]]n refugees. [[Federal Republic of Yugoslavia|Yugoslav]] officials say 75 people were killed. * 1999 &ndash; A [[1999 Sydney hailstorm|severe hailstorm]] strikes Sydney, Australia causing [[Australian dollar|A$]]2.3 billion in insured damages, the most costly natural disaster in Australian history. *[[2002]] &ndash; [[Venezuela]]n President [[Hugo Chávez]] returns to office two days after being ousted and arrested by the country's military. *[[2003]] &ndash; The [[Human Genome Project]] is completed with 99% of the human [[genome]] sequenced to an accuracy of 99.99%. * 2003 &ndash; U.S. troops in [[Baghdad]] capture [[Abu Abbas]], leader of the [[Palestinian people|Palestinian]] group that killed an American on the hijacked cruise liner the {{MS|Achille Lauro}} in [[1985]]. *[[2005]] &ndash; The [[Oregon Supreme Court]] nullifies marriage licenses issued to same-sex couples a year earlier by [[Multnomah County, Oregon|Multnomah County]]. *[[2010]] &ndash; Nearly 2,700 are killed in a [[2010 Yushu earthquake|magnitude 6.9 earthquake]] in the [[Yushu Tibetan Autonomous Prefecture]]. *[[2012]] &ndash; [[United Nations Security Council Resolution 2042]] relating to [[2011-2012 Syrian uprising|Syrian uprising]] is adopted. *[[2014]] &ndash; [[April 2014 Abuja bombing|Twin bomb blasts]] in [[Abuja|Abuja, Nigeria]], kill at least 75 people and injures 141 others. * 2014 &ndash; Two hundred seventy-six schoolgirls are [[Chibok schoolgirls kidnapping|abducted]] by [[Boko Haram]] in [[Chibok]], [[Nigeria]]. *[[2016]] &ndash; In Japan, the [[2016 Kumamoto earthquakes#April 14 Foreshock|foreshock]] of Kumamoto earthquakes occurs.
