est (b. 1720) *[[1843]] &ndash; [[Joseph Lanner]], Austrian violinist and composer (b. 1801) *[[1864]] &ndash; [[Charles Lot Church]], American-Canadian politician (b. 1777) *[[1910]] &ndash; [[Mikhail Vrubel]], Russian painter and sculptor (b. 1856) *[[1911]] &ndash; [[Addie Joss]], American baseball player and journalist (b. 1880) * 1911 &ndash; [[Henri Elzéar Taschereau]], Canadian lawyer and jurist, 4th [[Chief Justice of Canada]] (b. 1836) *[[1912]] &ndash; [[Henri Brisson]], French politician, 50th [[Prime Minister of France]] (b. 1835) *[[1914]] &ndash; [[Hubert Bland]], English activist, co-founded the [[Fabian Society]] (b. 1855) *[[1917]] &ndash; [[L. L. Zamenhof]], Polish physician and linguist, created [[Esperanto]] (b. 1859) *[[1919]] &ndash; [[Auguste-Réal Angers]], Canadian judge and politician, 6th [[Lieutenant Governor of Quebec]] (b. 1837) *[[1925]] &ndash; [[John Singer Sargent]], American painter (b. 1856) *[[1930]] &ndash; [[Vladimir Mayakovsky]], Georgian-Russian actor, playwright, and poet (b. 1893) *[[1931]] &ndash; [[Richard Armstedt]], German philologist, historian, and educator (b. 1851) *[[1935]] &ndash; [[Emmy Noether]], German-American mathematician and academic (b. 1882) *[[1938]] &ndash; [[Gillis Grafström]], Swedish figure skater and architect (b. 1893) *[[1943]] &ndash; [[Yakov Dzhugashvili]], Georgian-Russian lieutenant (b. 1907) *[[1950]] &ndash; [[Ramana Maharshi]], Indian guru and philosopher (b. 1879) *[[1951]] &ndash; [[Al Christie]], Canadian-American director, producer, and screenwriter (b. 1881) *[[1962]] &ndash; [[M. Visvesvaraya]], Indian engineer and scholar (b. 1860) *[[1963]] &ndash; [[Rahul Sankrityayan]], Indian monk and historian (b. 1893) *[[1964]] &ndash; [[Tatyana Afanasyeva]], Russian-Dutch mathematician and theorist (b. 1876) * 1964 &ndash; [[Rachel Carson]], American biologist and author (b. 1907) *[[1968]] &ndash; [[Al Benton]], American baseball player (b. 1911) *[[1969]] &ndash; [[Matilde Muñoz Sampedro]], 