{{Infobox recurring event | name = <!--Uses page name if omitted--> | logo = | logo_alt = | logo_caption = | logo_size = | image = | image_size = | alt = | caption = | status = active | genre = Family Festival | frequency = Annually | venue = {{Plainlist| * [[Bolesworth Estate]], [[Cheshire]], [[England]] * [[Laverstoke Park Farm]], [[Hampshire]], England }} | coordinates = <!-- {{coord|LAT|LON|type:event|display=inline,title}} --> | country = [[England]] | years_active = <!-- {{age|YYYY|mm|dd}} Date of the first occurrence --> | first = {{start date|2012|08}} | founder_name = [[Chris Evans (presenter)|Chris Evans]] | last = <!-- Date of most recent event; if the event will not be held again, use {{End date|YYYY|MM|DD|df=y}} --> | prev = | next = | participants = | attendance = | capacity = | area = | budget = | activity = | leader_name = | patron = | organised = <!-- "organized=" also works --> | people = | member = | sponsor = | website = }} {{coi|date=October 2018}} '''CarFest''' is an annual family music and motoring [[festival]] held in [[Cheshire]] and [[Hampshire]], England. It was founded by the radio presenter [[Chris Evans (presenter)|Chris Evans]] in 2012,<ref name="BBC-33886674">{{cite web|url=https://www.bbc.co.uk/news/entertainment-arts-33886674|title=Chris Evans puts Chitty Chitty Bang Bang car up for auction|date=12 August 2015|work=[[BBC Online]]|accessdate=12 August 2015}}</ref><ref name="Scullion">{{cite web|url=http://www.classiccarsforsale.co.uk/news/auction-news/1508/serial-carfest-charity-donor-gives-away-moggie-van-and-saloon/|title=Serial CarFest charity donor gives away Moggie van and saloon|last=Scullion|first=Murray|date=4 August 2015|work=Classic Cars For Sale UK|accessdate=12 August 2015}}</ref> and raises funds for [[Children in Need]], a British charity. The festival presents a variety of entertainment - live music performances, track shows, "[[celebrity chef]]" demos, driving experiences, a [[Live steam|steam fair]], a fundraising family fun run and a carnival fancy dress parade.
