{{Use dmy dates|date=July 2015}} {{Use Irish English|date=July 2015}} {{infobox music festival | | music_festival_name = The Flat Lake Literary & Arts Festival | location = [[Scotshouse]], [[Ireland]] | years_active= 2007–present | dates = 5 – 6 June 2010 | genre = Readings, [[Comedy]], [[Music]], [[Theatre]] | website = [http://www.theflatlakefestival.com Official website]}}
The '''Flat Lake Festival''' is an annual event organised by [[Patrick McCabe (novelist)]] and the Welsh film director [[Kevin Allen (actor)]] on the Hilton Park farm estate in [[Clones, County Monaghan|Clones]], [[Co. Monaghan]], first held in 2007. The attractions of the festival are readings, [[comedy]], [[music]] and [[theatre]] that take place among the barns and bales of hay, abandoned tractors and ancient oaks of the estate over the period of a long weekend, just a couple of miles outside the town of Clones on the back road to [[Cavan]] town.<ref>[https://www.independent.co.uk/arts-entertainment/art/reviews/flat-lake-literary--arts-festival-clones-co-monaghan-ireland-912103.html"] ''The Independent'' Friday, 29 August 2008</ref>¨[[nthWORD]] calls it a "cheap, off-beat, anarchic weekend that is hard to beat"<ref>{{cite web |url=http://shorts.nthword.com/2010/06/review-flat-lake-literary-arts-festival.html |title=Archived copy |accessdate=2010-06-10 |deadurl=yes |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20110407182927/http://shorts.nthword.com/2010/06/review-flat-lake-literary-arts-festival.html |archivedate=7 April 2011 |df=dmy-all }} ''nthWORD Magazine Shorts'' 9 June 2010</ref>
