[[Image:Oysterfestival.jpg|right|thumb|Logo for the Oyster Festival]] {{Update|date=February 2017}} The '''Norwalk Oyster Festival''' is an annual fair in the city of [[Norwalk, Connecticut]], United States, held on the first weekend after [[Labor Day]] in Veterans Park, near [[Long Island Sound]].
Funds raised by the festival help the Norwalk Seaport Association maintain the [[Sheffield Island Light]]house as well as develop science education classes. The festival is also used as a fundraiser by more than 20 other local non-profit organizations.
The festival has been run by the [http://seaport.org/ Norwalk Seaport Association], a [[non profit]] organization, since its inception in 1978. Average annual attendance exceeds 90,000. Each year, the Oyster Festival contributes over $5 million to the local economy. {{Citation needed|date=April 2010}}
It features various food, vendors, and entertainment, and celebrates the history of the [[oyster]] industry based in Norwalk. In the past, featured performers have included the [[Village People]], [[Kansas (band)|Kansas]], [[Charlie Daniels Band]], [[Joe Walsh]], [[Willie Nelson]], [[Blood, Sweat & Tears]], [[Tito Puente]], [[Cheap Trick]], [[Little Feat]], [[The Monkees]], [[Judy Collins]], [[Up with People]], and [[Little Richard]]. {{Citation needed|date=April 2010}}
==History== The 29th annual Oyster Festival took place Friday, September 8 to Sunday, September 10, 2006. [[Bo Bice]], [[Dion DiMucci|Dion]], and [[Asia (band)|Asia]] were featured performers.{{Citation needed|date=April 2010}}
The 30th annual festival took place September 7 to September 9, 2007 with the [[Village People]] heading up the entertainment, the band's third appearance. [[Jay and the Americans]] were also booked for the event.<ref name="mb1">{{cite news|last=Breslow|first=Matt|title=Village People will be main act at Oyster Festival|work=[[The Advocate (Stamford)|The Advocate]] Norwalk edition|location=[[Stamford, Connecticut]]|pages=1, A4}}</ref>
The 31st annual festival took place September 5 to September 7, 2008. The festival was called off on Saturday the 6th to accommodate the rain from [[Hurricane Hanna (2008)|Hurricane Hanna]].<ref name="kobak">{{cite news|last=Kobak|first=Steve|work=The Hour|title=Hanna has officials thinking twice about continuing Oyster Festival|pages=A1|volume=137|issue=244|date=2008-09-06|location=[[Norwalk, Connecticut]]}}</ref> [[Los Lonely Boys]] performed Friday evening and [[Kathy Sledge]] performed Sunday evening.<ref name="kobak"/>
==Incidents and accidents== On September 8, 2013, 17 children and one adult were injured in an [[amusement ride]] accident in when a [[swing ride]] suffered a mechanical failure. Several injured were transported to Norwalk, [[Stamford, Connecticut|Stamford]] and [[Bridgeport, Connecticut|Bridgeport]] hospitals. None of the injuries were life-threatening.<ref>{{cite web|title=18 injured after carnival ride accident in Norwalk|url=http://abclocal.go.com/wabc/story?section=news/local/northern_suburbs&id=9240648|publisher=WABC TV|accessdate=9 September 2013}}</ref>
[[Image:Carl Palmer 7040.jpg|thumb|[[Carl Palmer]] of [[Asia (band)|Asia]] at the 29th Norwalk Oyster Festival on September 10, 2006]]
