{{short description|Showcase of a capella music hosted by members of tech companies in Silicon Valley}} {{Infobox music festival | name =Techapella | location =[[Silicon Valley]] | years_active =2013-present | genre = [[A Cappella]] | website =[http://www.techapella.com Techapella] }}
'''Techapella''' is an annual showcase of [[a cappella]] music hosted by members of tech companies in [[Silicon Valley]], [[California]]. The event was founded in 2013 by Laolee Xiong and Aaron Roan, members of [[Facebook]]'s The Vocal Network and [[Google]]'s Googapella, respectively.<ref name="lee">{{cite web|url=https://www.sfchronicle.com/business/article/Techies-tune-up-for-Pitch-Perfect-style-a-6682050.php|title=Techies tune up for ‘Pitch Perfect’-style a cappella showcase|last=Lee|first=Wendy|date=2015-12-07|newspaper=[[San Francisco Chronicle]]|accessdate=2018-10-14}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=https://news.vice.com/en_us/article/xw4zqq/watch-google-facebook-apple-twitter-and-pinterest-battle-in-a-pitch-perfect-sing-off|title=Watch Silicon Valley Nerds Face Off A Capella|publisher=[[Vice News]]|last=Justus|first=Matthew|accessdate=2018-10-15|date=2017-12-17}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://nymag.com/selectall/2017/10/silicon-valley-a-cappella-techapella.html|title=Silicon Valley Has Gone All-In on A Cappella|work=[[New York Magazine]]|accessdate=2018-10-15|date=2017-10-05|last=Pressler|first=Jessica}}</ref>
The event has been emceed by a cappella personality and Sing-Off producer [[Deke Sharon]],<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.theguardian.com/technology/2017/dec/19/techapella-a-cappella-facebook-google-twitter|publisher=[[The Guardian]]|title= Welcome to Techapella, where top firms trade hashtags for harmonies|date=2017-12-19 |accessdate = 2018-10-15|last=Solon|first=Olivia}}</ref><ref name="lee"/> and is used as a fundraiser for local charities Music for Minors and the [[San Francisco Conservatory of Music]].<ref name="sfcm">{{cite web | url=https://sfcm.edu/events/techapella-2018 | title=Techapella 2018|publisher=[[San Francisco Conservatory of Music]]|accessdate=2018-10-15}}</ref>
Participating groups have included Googapella and Alphabeat (made up of Google employees), The Vocal Network (Facebook), The Pintunes ([[Pinterest]]), InTune ([[LinkedIn]]), Songbirds ([[Twitter]]), The Square Registers ([[Square, Inc.|Square]]), Syncopation ([[Dropbox (service)|Dropbox]]), AirBnBeats ([[AirBnB]]), The Keynotes ([[Apple Inc.|Apple]]), The Chromotones ([[23andMe]]), and Scalesforce ([[Salesforce]]).<ref>{{cite web | url=https://www.techapella.com/ | title=Welcome|publisher=Techapella|accessdate=2018-10-15}}</ref>
